{"type":"text","timestamp":1775848066336,"sessionID":"ses_28735da7cffeKZi0BV2UsN2PY9","part":{"id":"prt_d78cb0a74001pO1t7NNL5pGoWj","messageID":"msg_d78cb0181001KSSBjxNZLy0L2p","sessionID":"ses_28735da7cffeKZi0BV2UsN2PY9","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context to write a comprehensive proposal.md for AR-009. Let me create the proposal following the established pattern from AR-005.","time":{"start":1775848066334,"end":1775848066334}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848160482,"sessionID":"ses_28735da7cffeKZi0BV2UsN2PY9","part":{"id":"prt_d78cb0d20001VNdcUkaX0wIHgM","messageID":"msg_d78cb0181001KSSBjxNZLy0L2p","sessionID":"ses_28735da7cffeKZi0BV2UsN2PY9","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_5e37cc1375e2459ea807ae02","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md","content":"# AR-009: Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal defines the HTTP reverse proxy core implementation for the `pkg/router` module in the AgentCube project. The router is responsible for:\n\n1. **Session-aware traffic routing** - Resolve or create sessions via workload manager, route HTTP requests to appropriate sandbox endpoints\n2. **Reverse proxy functionality** - Proxy HTTP traffic to sandbox pods with proper URL rewriting and header forwarding\n3. **JWT authentication** - Sign outbound requests to sandboxes with JWT tokens for authentication\n4. **Connection management** - Handle connection pooling, health checks, and concurrency limiting\n5. **Activity tracking** - Update session last-activity timestamps in the store for idle cleanup\n\nThe router serves as the primary entry point for all HTTP invocations targeting agent runtimes and code interpreters.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **Session Manager** (`pkg/router/session/manager.go`)\n   - `SessionManager` interface and implementation\n   - Session resolution from `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n   - Workload manager integration for session creation\n   - `SandboxInfo` caching and lookup\n\n2. **Reverse Proxy Core** (`pkg/router/proxy/proxy.go`)\n   - `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy` wrapper\n   - Custom `Director` for URL rewriting and header injection\n   - JWT generation and injection for sandbox authentication\n   - Error handling and response mapping\n\n3. **Routing Rules Engine** (`pkg/router/routing/rules.go`)\n   - Entry point selection by path matching\n   - Protocol normalization (http/https)\n   - URL scheme detection and prefixing\n\n4. **Connection Pooling** (`pkg/router/pool/pool.go`)\n   - Shared `http.Transport` configuration\n   - Connection reuse settings\n   - Idle connection management\n\n5. **Health Check System** (`pkg/router/health/checker.go`)\n   - Liveness endpoint (`/health/live`)\n   - Readiness endpoint (`/health/ready`)\n   - Dependency health verification\n\n6. **HTTP Server** (`pkg/router/server.go`)\n   - Gin router setup with middleware stack\n   - HTTP/2 and h2c support\n   - TLS configuration\n   - Graceful shutdown\n\n7. **Middleware Components**\n   - Concurrency limiting semaphore (`pkg/router/middleware/semaphore.go`)\n   - Gin logger and recovery\n   - Forwarding headers injection (`X-Forwarded-Host`, `X-Forwarded-Proto`, `X-Forwarded-For`)\n\n8. **JWT Manager** (`pkg/router/auth/jwt.go`)\n   - RS256 JWT signing\n   - Key generation and storage (`picod-router-identity` secret)\n   - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` bootstrap logic\n\n9. **Invocation Handlers** (`pkg/router/handler/invocation.go`)\n   - AgentRuntime invocation endpoint\n   - CodeInterpreter invocation endpoint\n   - Session resolution and activity tracking\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Workload Manager reconciler logic (separate controller component)\n- Session store implementation (uses existing `pkg/store` module)\n- CRD type definitions (defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`)\n- Python SDK CLI commands (separate Python package)\n- PicoD daemon inside sandboxes (separate `picod` binary)\n- Agentd idle cleanup controller (separate controller component)\n- Volcano scheduler integration (optional, separate component)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Type | Reason |\n|------------|------|--------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Required | Generated Kubernetes client for Secret operations |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | Required | In-cluster config, Secret API |\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Required | Secret, ServiceAccount types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | Required | Kubernetes error handling |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | Required | HTTP framework |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | Required | JWT signing (RS256) |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Required | Session store client |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Required | Session store interface |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Required | Type constants (kinds) |\n| `net/http/httputil` | Required | Reverse proxy |\n| `golang.org/x/net/http2` | Required | HTTP/2 support |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **External Clients** - HTTP API consumers invoking agent runtimes\n2. **Python SDK** - Uses router endpoints for invocation\n3. **CLI Tool** - Routes commands through router\n4. **Agentd Controller** - Monitors session activity timestamps\n5. **Workload Manager** - Receives session creation requests from router\n\n### Breaking Changes\n\nNone — this is the initial implementation of the router module.\n\n### Migration Path\n\nNot applicable for initial implementation. Future migrations may include:\n- JWT algorithm migration (RS256 → ES256)\n- Session ID format changes (UUID → nanoid)\n- Protocol versioning (HTTP/1.1 → HTTP/2 mandatory)\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use Envoy as Data Plane\n\n**Approach:** Deploy Envoy sidecar or standalone proxy, configure via xDS API.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Industry-standard proxy with extensive features\n- Built-in observability (metrics, tracing)\n- Advanced load balancing algorithms\n- Automatic retries and circuit breaking\n\n**Cons:**\n- Significant operational complexity\n- Requires xDS control plane implementation\n- Over-engineering for single-tenant routing\n- Steeper learning curve for debugging\n- Additional resource overhead\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Envoy is overkill for AgentCube's use case; Go's built-in `httputil.ReverseProxy` provides sufficient functionality with simpler operations.\n\n### Alternative 2: Use Traefik or Kong API Gateway\n\n**Approach:** Deploy off-the-shelf API gateway, configure via CRDs or admin API.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Rich feature set out of the box\n- Managed authentication/authorization\n- Plugin ecosystem\n- Dashboard and observability\n\n**Cons:**\n- Less control over session logic\n- Custom middleware development still required\n- Additional deployment complexity\n- Licensing considerations (Kong)\n- Tight coupling to external project\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Custom implementation provides full control over session-aware routing logic and aligns with AgentCube's Kubernetes-native architecture.\n\n### Alternative 3: Direct Client-to-Sandbox Routing\n\n**Approach:** Clients discover sandbox IPs directly from Kubernetes API, bypass router.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Eliminates proxy hop (lower latency)\n- Simpler architecture (one less component)\n- No single point of failure\n\n**Cons:**\n- Exposes internal pod IPs to clients\n- No centralized session management\n- Clients must handle Kubernetes API complexity\n- No JWT injection for sandbox authentication\n- Harder to implement idle cleanup\n- Security concerns (direct pod access)\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Router provides essential abstraction layer for session management, security, and lifecycle tracking.\n\n### Alternative 4: Use Kubernetes Service Mesh (Istio/Linkerd)\n\n**Approach:** Leverage service mesh for traffic routing and authentication.\n\n**Pros:**\n- mTLS between services\n- Advanced traffic management\n- Observability built-in\n- Policy enforcement\n\n**Cons:**\n- Massive operational overhead\n- Requires mesh installation on all clusters\n- Complex configuration (VirtualServices, DestinationRules)\n- Over-engineering for simple proxy use case\n- Performance overhead from sidecars\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Service mesh is unnecessary complexity; router is a single, focused component with minimal dependencies.\n\n### Alternative 5: WebSocket-Only Proxy\n\n**Approach:** Use WebSocket connections for all sandbox communication instead of HTTP proxy.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Persistent connections (lower latency for repeated calls)\n- Full-duplex communication\n- Better for streaming use cases\n\n**Cons:**\n- Breaking change for HTTP clients\n- More complex connection management\n- Harder to debug (non-standard tooling)\n- Load balancers may not support WebSocket well\n- Session state tied to connection lifetime\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. HTTP proxy is more compatible with existing tools and client libraries; WebSocket can be added as future enhancement.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation (Week 1)\n\n1. **Scaffold Directory Structure**\n   ```\n   pkg/router/\n   ├── server.go              # HTTP server setup\n   ├── session/\n   │   ├── manager.go         # SessionManager interface\n   │   ├── sandbox_info.go    # SandboxInfo type\n   │   └── errors.go          # Session-related errors\n   ├── proxy/\n   │   ├── proxy.go           # ReverseProxy wrapper\n   │   ├── director.go        # Request director\n   │   └── transport.go       # HTTP transport config\n   ├── routing/\n   │   ├── rules.go           # Routing rules engine\n   │   └── entry_point.go     # Entry point selection\n   ├── auth/\n   │   ├── jwt.go             # JWTManager, signing\n   │   └── keys.go            # Key generation/storage\n   ├── middleware/\n   │   ├── semaphore.go       # Concurrency limiter\n   │   ├── headers.go         # Forwarding headers\n   │   └── logger.go          # Request logging\n   ├── health/\n   │   └── checker.go         # Health endpoints\n   ├── pool/\n   │   └── pool.go            # Connection pooling\n   └── handler/\n       └── invocation.go      # Invocation handlers\n   ```\n\n2. **Define Core Interfaces**\n   - `SessionManager` interface\n   - `Proxy` interface\n   - `JWTManager` interface\n\n3. **Implement Session Manager**\n   - Load session from store by ID\n   - Create session via workload manager POST\n   - Cache `SandboxInfo` in memory\n\n### Phase 2: Proxy Core (Week 2)\n\n4. **Implement ReverseProxy Wrapper**\n   - Wrap `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy`\n   - Custom `Director` function\n   - Error handler for connection failures\n\n5. **Implement JWT Manager**\n   - Generate RS256 key pair\n   - Store/load from Kubernetes Secret\n   - Sign JWT with sandbox claims\n\n6. **Implement Routing Rules**\n   - Path-based entry point matching\n   - Protocol normalization\n   - URL scheme detection\n\n### Phase 3: HTTP Server (Week 3)\n\n7. **Implement HTTP Server**\n   - Gin router setup\n   - HTTP/2 and h2c configuration\n   - TLS support (optional)\n   - Graceful shutdown\n\n8. **Add Middleware Stack**\n   - Concurrency semaphore\n   - Gin logger and recovery\n   - Forwarding headers injection\n\n9. **Implement Health Endpoints**\n   - `/health/live` - always returns 200\n   - `/health/ready` - checks session manager availability\n\n### Phase 4: Integration (Week 4)\n\n10. **Implement Invocation Handlers**\n    - AgentRuntime invocation (`POST /v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`)\n    - CodeInterpreter invocation (`POST /v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path`)\n    - Session resolution and activity tracking\n\n11. **Write Unit Tests**\n    - Session manager tests with mock store\n    - Proxy tests with test HTTP server\n    - JWT tests with key generation\n    - Routing rule tests\n\n12. **Write Integration Tests**\n    - End-to-end invocation flow\n    - Session creation and reuse\n    - Error handling scenarios\n    - Concurrency limit enforcement\n\n## Router Architecture\n\n### Request Flow\n\n```\nClient Request\n    ↓\n[1] Extract x-agentcube-session-id header\n    ↓\n[2] Session Manager: Load or Create\n    ├── If header empty → POST to WorkloadManager\n    └── If header present → Load from Store\n    ↓\n[3] Get SandboxInfo with EntryPoints\n    ↓\n[4] Select Entry Point by path matching\n    ↓\n[5] Build upstream URL (protocol + endpoint)\n    ↓\n[6] Generate JWT (RS256) for sandbox authentication\n    ↓\n[7] ReverseProxy with custom Director\n    ├── Set Host, Path\n    ├── Inject Authorization: Bearer <JWT>\n    ├── Set X-Forwarded-* headers\n    └── Apply concurrency semaphore\n    ↓\n[8] Update LastActivity timestamp in Store\n    ↓\nSandbox Pod (with PicoD daemon)\n```\n\n### Concurrency Model\n\n```\n┌───────────────────────────────────────┐\n│         Semaphore (capacity: 1000)    │\n└───────────────────────────────────────┘\n                    ↓\n    ┌───────────────┼───────────────┐\n    ↓               ↓               ↓\n[Request 1]   [Request 2]   [Request N]\n    ↓               ↓               ↓\n[Session Res] [Session Res] [Session Res]\n    ↓               ↓               ↓\n[JWT Gen]     [JWT Gen]     [JWT Gen]\n    ↓               ↓               ↓\n[ReverseProxy] [ReverseProxy] [ReverseProxy]\n    ↓               ↓               ↓\n[Sandbox 1]    [Sandbox 2]    [Sandbox N]\n```\n\n### Error Handling Matrix\n\n| Error Type | HTTP Status | Response Body |\n|------------|-------------|---------------|\n| Session not found | 404 | `{\"error\":\"session not found\",\"sessionId\":\"...\"}` |\n| Sandbox template not found | 404 | `{\"error\":\"sandbox template not found\",\"namespace\":\"...\",\"name\":\"...\"}` |\n| No entry points | 404 | `{\"error\":\"no entry point found for sandbox\"}` |\n| JWT signing failure | 500 | `{\"error\":\"failed to sign request\",\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"}` |\n| Connection refused | 502 | `{\"error\":\"sandbox unreachable\"}` |\n| Connection timeout | 504 | `{\"error\":\"sandbox timeout\"}` |\n| Other proxy error | 502 | `{\"error\":\"sandbox unreachable\"}` |\n| Concurrency limit exceeded | 429 | `{\"error\":\"server overloaded, please try again later\",\"code\":\"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}` |\n| Session manager not ready | 503 | `{\"error\":\"session manager not available\",\"status\":\"not ready\"}` |\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n### Invocation Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Invoke AgentRuntime sandbox |\n| `GET` | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Invoke AgentRuntime sandbox (GET) |\n| `POST` | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Invoke CodeInterpreter sandbox |\n| `GET` | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Invoke CodeInterpreter sandbox (GET) |\n\n### Health Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/health/live` | Liveness probe |\n| `GET` | `/health/ready` | Readiness probe |\n\n### Request/Response Examples\n\n**Create Session (via WorkloadManager):**\n```http\nPOST /v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/chat HTTP/1.1\nHost: router.agentcube.local\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\"message\":\"hello\"}\n```\n\n**Internal WorkloadManager Request:**\n```http\nPOST {WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime HTTP/1.1\nContent-Type: application/json\nAuthorization: Bearer <service-account-token>\n\n{\n  \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n  \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\"\n}\n```\n\n**WorkloadManager Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"sess-abc123\",\n  \"sandboxName\": \"my-agent-sandbox-x7y9z\",\n  \"entryPoints\": [\n    {\"protocol\":\"http\",\"endpoint\":\"10.244.1.5:8080\",\"path\":\"/chat\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Proxied Request to Sandbox:**\n```http\nPOST /chat HTTP/1.1\nHost: 10.244.1.5:8080\nAuthorization: Bearer <jwt-signed-token>\nX-Forwarded-Host: router.agentcube.local\nX-Forwarded-Proto: http\nX-Forwarded-For: 192.168.1.100\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```http\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\nx-agentcube-session-id: sess-abc123\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\"response\":\"hello back\"}\n```\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] SessionManager resolves existing sessions from store\n- [ ] SessionManager creates new sessions via WorkloadManager when header missing\n- [ ] ReverseProxy correctly routes to sandbox endpoints\n- [ ] JWT injected for sandbox kinds (Sandbox, SandboxClaim)\n- [ ] Forwarding headers set correctly (X-Forwarded-Host, X-Forwarded-Proto, X-Forwarded-For)\n- [ ] Health endpoints respond correctly (live/ready)\n- [ ] Concurrency limiter enforces MaxConcurrentRequests\n- [ ] Connection pooling configured with shared Transport\n- [ ] Error mapping matches specification (404, 502, 504, 429, 503)\n- [ ] Session last-activity updated on successful invoke\n- [ ] HTTP/2 and h2c support working\n- [ ] TLS configuration optional but functional\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown within 10s\n- [ ] Unit test coverage >80%\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with test Kubernetes cluster\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **SessionManager Tests**\n   - `TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_MissingHeader`\n   - `TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_NotFound`\n   - `TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_WorkloadManagerCreate`\n   - `TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_WorkloadManagerError`\n   - `TestSessionManager_UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n\n2. **ReverseProxy Tests**\n   - `TestProxy_Director_PathNormalization`\n   - `TestProxy_Director_HeaderInjection`\n   - `TestProxy_ErrorHandler_ConnectionRefused`\n   - `TestProxy_ErrorHandler_Timeout`\n   - `TestProxy_Transport_Reuse`\n\n3. **JWTManager Tests**\n   - `TestJWTManager_GenerateToken`\n   - `TestJWTManager_VerifyToken`\n   - `TestJWTManager_TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret_Create`\n   - `TestJWTManager_TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret_Load`\n\n4. **Routing Tests**\n   - `TestRoutingRules_SelectEntryPoint_MatchByPath`\n   - `TestRoutingRules_SelectEntryPoint_FirstEntry`\n   - `TestRoutingRules_NormalizeProtocol`\n   - `TestRoutingRules_DetectScheme`\n\n5. **Middleware Tests**\n   - `TestSemaphoreMiddleware_LimitEnforcement`\n   - `TestSemaphoreMiddleware_Release`\n   - `TestHeadersMiddleware_XForwardedHeaders`\n\n6. **Health Tests**\n   - `TestHealthChecker_Live`\n   - `TestHealthChecker_Ready_WithManager`\n   - `TestHealthChecker_Ready_WithoutManager`\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **End-to-End Invocation Flow**\n   - Start test router server\n   - Mock WorkloadManager with test HTTP server\n   - Mock Redis store with test instance\n   - Create invocation request without session header\n   - Verify session creation and proxy to sandbox\n\n2. **Session Reuse**\n   - Create session once\n   - Send multiple requests with session header\n   - Verify no additional WorkloadManager calls\n   - Verify LastActivity updates\n\n3. **Error Scenarios**\n   - WorkloadManager returns 404\n   - Sandbox pod not reachable\n   - JWT signing failure\n   - Concurrency limit exceeded\n\n4. **Concurrency Test**\n   - Send N concurrent requests (N > limit)\n   - Verify some requests get 429\n   - Verify successful requests complete\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|------------|------------|\n| WorkloadManager unavailable | High | Medium | Cache sessions; return cached SandboxInfo if manager down; add circuit breaker |\n| Redis store unavailable | High | Low | In-memory fallback for session cache; log warnings; degrade gracefully |\n| JWT key secret creation fails | High | Low | Fail server startup; clear error message; manual secret creation fallback |\n| Connection exhaustion | Medium | Medium | Configure Transport.MaxIdleConns, MaxIdleConnsPerHost; monitor connection metrics |\n| Memory leak from session cache | Medium | Medium | Implement LRU eviction; TTL-based cleanup; integrate with agentd |\n| HTTP/2 h2c compatibility | Low | Medium | Test with major HTTP clients; fallback to HTTP/1.1 if negotiation fails |\n| Race condition in LastActivity | Low | Medium | Use atomic operations or mutex; accept eventual consistency |\n| Sandbox IP changes | Medium | Low | Refresh SandboxInfo on connection failure; implement retry with fresh lookup |\n\n## Future Considerations\n\n1. **Circuit Breaker Pattern** - Implement circuit breaker for WorkloadManager calls\n2. **Metrics and Observability** - Add Prometheus metrics (request latency, error rates, concurrency usage)\n3. **Distributed Tracing** - Integrate OpenTelemetry for request tracing across components\n4. **Rate Limiting** - Per-client or per-session rate limiting beyond global concurrency\n5. **Request/Response Logging** - Structured logging for audit and debugging\n6. **WebSocket Support** - Upgrade HTTP connections to WebSocket for streaming use cases\n7. **Session Affinity** - Sticky sessions for multi-replica router deployments\n8. **Hot Reload** - Dynamic configuration reload without restart\n9. **Multi-Cluster Routing** - Route to sandboxes across multiple Kubernetes clusters\n10. **Canary Deployments** - Traffic splitting for sandbox version upgrades\n\n## References\n\n- [net/http/httputil.ReverseProxy](https://pkg.go.dev/net/http/httputil#ReverseProxy)\n- [Gin Web Framework](https://gin-gonic.com/)\n- [golang-jwt/jwt](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt)\n- [HTTP/2 and h2c](https://httpwg.org/specs/rfc7540.html)\n- Session Routing Spec: `session-routing/spec.md`\n- Deployment Spec: `deployment/spec.md`\n- Client-go Documentation: `deployment/client-go.md`\n- Related: `changes/AR-004/` (WorkloadManager HTTP Service)\n- Related: `changes/AR-008/` (Session Store)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775848160464,"end":1775848160477}}}}
